Apache Flink integration with OCI Object Storage
Created by Marek Kratky, last updated on Nov 14, 2025  2 minute read

Apache Flink is a framework and distributed processing engine for stateful computations over unbounded and bounded data streams. 

Apache Flink uses file systems to consume and persistently store data, both for the results of applications and for fault tolerance and recovery. These are some of most of the popular file systems, including local, hadoop-compatible, Amazon S3, Aliyun OSS and Azure Blob Storage. See https://nightlies.apache.org/flink/flink-docs-release-2.1/docs/deployment/filesystems/overview/ for more details. 




OCI Object Storage is not listed as the Apache Flink supported file system however it can be integrated using Amazon S3 compatibility or HDFS Connector interfaces.  

Apache Flink Amazon S3 configuration is described here: https://nightlies.apache.org/flink/flink-docs-master/docs/deployment/filesystems/s3/

OCI Object Storage S3 support is described in this doc: https://docs.oracle.com/en-us/iaas/Content/Object/Tasks/s3compatibleapi.htm




OCI Object Storage S3 endpoint is provided in 2 styles and both are applicable in this scenario:

Virtual host style URL: https://vhcompat.objectstorage.<region>.oci.customer-oci.com
or
Path style access: https://<namespace>.compat.objectstorage.<region>.oci.customer-oci.com

 

S3 access and secret key are required:

We can generate the access and secret key for a specific OCI user under Tokens and Keys -> Customer secret keys

https://docs.public.content.oci.oraclecloud.com/en-us/iaas/Content/Identity/access/to_create_a_Customer_Secret_key.htm

 

This OCI user needs to be in a group which is allowed to manage the objects in the bucket by IAM policy:

https://docs.oracle.com/en-us/iaas/Content/Security/Reference/objectstorage_security.htm#iam-policies




Step-by-step guide

The following steps are involved in setting up the Apache Flink file system using S3 interface

 download the latest binary release of Flink, then extract the archive
Inside the flink directory:
mkdir ./plugins/s3-fs-hadoop  
cp ./opt/flink-s3-fs-hadoop-2.1.1.jar ./plugins/s3-fs-hadoop/
Edit the conf/config.yaml with the following settings:

s3.access-key: my_access_key
s3.secret-key: my_secret_key
s3.endpoint: https://<namespace>.compat.objectstorage.<region>.oci.customer-oci.com
s3.path.style.access: true

execution:
  checkpointing:
    interval: 3min
    externalized-checkpoint-retention: RETAIN_ON_CANCELLATION
    max-concurrent-checkpoints: 1
    min-pause: 0
    mode: EXACTLY_ONCE
    timeout: 10min
    tolerable-failed-checkpoints: 0
    unaligned: false
    incremental: false
    dir: s3://flink/checkpoints/
    savepoint-dir: s3://flink/savepoints/

Create a bucket called e.g. “flink” in your tenancy
Start the cluster ./bin/start-cluster.sh
Run the sample application ./bin/flink run examples/streaming/WordCount.jar
Check the "flink" bucket and there should be following objects created: 

Buckets
  Flink
    Objects
      chekpoints/.../
        shared/
        taskowned
      



